Analysed findings of the 1946 cohort study and the Women in Employment survey from 1980. In 1946, lots of stay at home mothering but also women returning to work when the children were older. Middle c
lass women stayed out of work longer. Working class women were in employment for longer. By the 1980s, the social gradient had reversed. 
