ut were only gradually kicking in. Found that part-time work was worse pay as a result of deregulation brought in by Thatcher. Recommended better employment tribunals or a standard minimum wage for all work (full or part-time). 
\par Finds that change moves at a
 glacial pace. Her job is to keep monitoring it. Not interested in any sort of activism for change. Discusses the gap between research and action. Only recently have academic departments started having communications departments to publicise their finding
s and recommendations. 
\par Became Professor of Economic Demography, and Deputy Director of Social Statistics Research Unit at City University in 1994 and then carried on the same research as Deputy Director of the Centre for Longitudinal Studies in 1998}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
